a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><span>Gene K=
leiner was one of the iconic </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirec=
t/15b39ff6-c8b0-47a2-a654-e7895512ea9a?r=3D9p0gt" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: =
#1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">Traitorous Eight</a><span> employees =
who decided to leave the Shockley Semiconductor Laboratory to found Fairchi=
ld Semiconductor. His new partner Tom Perkins had learned directly from Dav=
id Packard at HP. When they joined forces to start a fund, venture capital =
was still a nascent practice. </span><strong>There was no such thing as dea=
l flow for VCs</strong><span>. According to Kleiner, &#8220;We just didn&#8=
217;t wait around for deals to come to us. You had to create the deals to b=
e really successful.&#8221;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size=
: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><span>In practice, this mean=
t partnering with university professors or entrepreneurs from existing larg=
e companies, and taking active management positions in the new ventures. An=
 example of this is </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/3b74e56=
7-f35f-4b85-bf3e-a60f3d63b86c?r=3D9p0gt" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; =
text-decoration: underline;">Tandem Computers</a><span>, one of the fund&#8=
217;s early wins. The company sold fault-tolerant computer systems. The CEO=
 was Jimmy Treybig, a former HP colleague. Tom Perkins served as the chairm=
an of the company from when it was founded until a merger over 20 years lat=
er.</span></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><span>Obviously, a lot has changed in the 50 years s=
ince Kleiner Perkins first opened its doors on Sand Hill Road. The computer=
 industry has exploded, giving birth to the software industry and the Web. =
</span><strong>With each generation, founders have gotten younger and compa=
nies have become more massive.</strong><span> While the first founders of K=
leiner Perkins portfolio companies were former colleagues with deep roots i=
n the early computer industry, the list now includes Larry Page and Sergey =
Brin, the brilliant young computer scientists who dropped out of their PhDs=
 at Stanford to found Google.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><span>The trend hasn=
&#8217;t stopped there. A more recent Kleiner Perkins investment is </span>=
<a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/e28514c0-6cb1-43e3-86fc-2dd16d0de0=
a2?r=3D9p0gt" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;=
">Figma</a><span>, the popular design tool that Packaso McCormick uses to m=
ake graphics for Not Boring. They have delivered on their </span><a href=3D=
"https://substack.com/redirect/b6acbd27-fea6-41c5-abba-5d6fe743cf53?r=3D9p0=
gt" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">early vi=
sion</a><span> of building a tool that would &#8220;allow users to creative=
ly express themselves online.&#8221; Figma was founded by Dylan Field and E=
van Wallace who met while undergrads at Brown. Dylan was awarded the </span=
><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/af73398e-4989-4e2f-beac-06b685e38=
c1a?r=3D9p0gt" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline=
;">Thiel Fellowship</a><span> to drop out of college and work on Figma full=
 time. A 2013 TechCrunch </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/20=
d435be-b752-4561-a769-c2a2d59a43a1?r=3D9p0gt" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1=
a1a; text-decoration: underline;">article</a><span> covering Figma&#8217;s =
$3.8 million seed round summed it up nicely saying, &#8220;</span><strong>C=
hildren are our future, and VCs are giving them the cash to make it happen.=
</strong><span>&#8221;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><span>A lot had to happen for tec=
h to reach this stage. Computers had to become substantially cheaper, faste=
r, and more widespread. An enormous amount of engineering had to happen to =
make computer science more accessible and standardized. Programming languag=
es had to evolve to more closely approximate natural language, encapsulatin=
g lower level details with clever abstractions. Modern browsers are so comp=
lex that even brilliant programmers like John Carmack struggle to </span><a=
 href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/92fddb86-1dc6-4f45-bd19-1ff588b3960a=
?r=3D9p0gt" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">=
keep track of all of the steps</a><span> involved in rendering the text you=
&#8217;re reading now. But browsers have a crucial property: </span><strong=
>they provide a nearly universal platform that can be used to build new pla=
tforms.</strong><span> The browser was the core platform that enabled two b=
rilliant young people to launch a company providing a new platform for crea=
tive expression. It took several layers of platforms to launch </span><a hr=
ef=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/7407c205-681f-495c-9a1b-65c06ff114ca?r=
=3D9p0gt" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">Th=
e Great Online Game</a><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">In most cases, biotech co=
mpany creation looks nothing like the current paradigm in tech. Current bio=
tech venture capital much more closely resembles the state of affairs 50 ye=
ars ago when Kleiner Perkins was founded. The first generation of specialis=
t biotech investors followed a similar playbook to the Tandem Computers day=
s. The process involved identifying promising science from academic labs an=
d building out a management team to commercialize it, with venture capitali=
sts often taking an active role.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><strong>More recently, this pr=
ocess has been systematized by venture creation funds and companies.</stron=
g><span> Some of the funds most commonly associated with this strategy are =
</span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/86f237a2-b5c6-48fa-a5ad-6b4=
f84b8f0a4?r=3D9p0gt" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: und=
erline;">Atlas</a><span>, </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/8=
